115.5	Deepak_Chopra	Deepak Chopra	Deepak Chopra (Hindi: ; born October 22, 1946) is an Indian-born, American physician, public speaker, and writer. He is generally specialized in subjects such as spirituality, Ayurveda and mind-body medicine. Chopra began his career as an endocrinologist and later shifted his focus to alternative medicine. He now runs his own medical center with a focus on mind-body connections. He is also a lecturer at the Update in Internal Medicine event, sponsored by Harvard Medical School's Department of Continuing Education and the Department of Medicine.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Deepak_Chopra_MSPAC.jpg/220px-Deepak_Chopra_MSPAC.jpg
